Function Parameter
--------------------------------
Function parameters are the values or arguments which are passed to a function.
In typescript, compiler accepts the same number and type of arguments as defined in the function signature.
If the compiler does not match the same parameters as in the function signature then it will give the compilation error.

Optional parameter

Default parameter

Rest parameter

Optional parameter
-----------------------------
In javascript we can all a function without passing any arguments.
So in javascript the parameter is optional and when we do this, each parameter value is undefined.

In typescript compiler will throw error if we try to invoke a function without providing the exact number of parameters as declared in its function signature.

To overcome this problem we can use optional parameters by using the question mark sign (?). It means that the parameters which may or may not receive a value can be appended by ? sign to make or mark them as optional.


function studentDetails(stdid:number,stdname:string,stdemail?:string)
{
console.log("student id is ",stdid);
console.log("student name is ",stdname);
-- if(stdemail!=undefined)
-- {
-- console.log("student email is ",stdemail);
-- }
}

studentDetails(45,"srinivas");//
studentDetails(45,"srinivas","chsr1207@ymail.com");

